# Loose Emerald Cut Diamond: Why 2ct Lab Beats 1ct Natural (Prices, Grades & What to Look For)

A loose emerald cut diamond starts at [$3,140 for a GIA 1ct D-VS1 Ideal](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29333987?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). A lab-grown 2ct D-FL Ideal costs [$4,735](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28828463?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — for $1,595 more, you double the carat weight and jump from D-VS1 to D-FL. That's the value inversion most buyers never see coming.

Lab 4ct D-VVS1 Excellent: [$7,737](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29587315?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Lab 5ct E-VVS1 Excellent: [$8,210](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28857918?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). The numbers don't lie.

